Feature: Get xray-connector configuration at run time

    As Xray Connector, I want to retrieve configuration information.

    # Rules:
    #
    # 1) This configuration should include:
    #
    # - JIRA host address: mandatory, defaults to 'jira.dt.renault.com'
    # - JIRA login: optional
    # - JIRA password: optional
    # - JIRA token: opetional
    #
    # - Xray reference test plan to use for downloading tests/feature files from Xray: mandatory
    # - Xray environment to use in reports publication: optional
    #
    # - Directory where to store feature files: mandatory, defaults to 'downloaded-features'
    # - Directory where to retrieve individual feature execution reports: mandatory, defaults to 'reports/cucumber/features'
    # - Directory where to store merged execution report: mandatory, defaults to 'reports/cucumber/merged'
    #
    # - Xray test execution custom fields ids
    #
    # 2) An error should be raised if a mandatory configuration parameter is not defined
    # 3) No error should be raised if an optional configuration parameter is not defined
    # 4) Either login and password, a session id or a token must be defined

    Scenario: Read JIRA host address configuration

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_HOST' environment variable has been set to 'HOST'
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA host configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'HOST'

    Scenario: Read JIRA login configuration

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_LOGIN' environment variable has been set to 'LOGIN'
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA login configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'LOGIN'

    Scenario: Read JIRA password configuration (JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD)

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD' environment variable has been set to 'PASSWORD'
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA password configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'PASSWORD'

    Scenario: Read JIRA password configuration (JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD)

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD' environment variable has been set to 'PASSWD'
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA password configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'PASSWD'

    Scenario: Read JIRA password configuration (both JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD and JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD defined)

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD' environment variable has been set to 'PASSWORD'
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD' environment variable has been set to 'PASSWD'
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA password configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'PASSWORD'

    Scenario: Read JIRA token configuration

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_TOKEN' environment variable has been set to 'TOKEN'
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA token configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'TOKEN'

    Scenario: Authentication cookie as an authentication method should be reported as a deprecated feature

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_COOKIE' environment variable has been set to 'COOKIE'
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA credentials configuration
        Then  A configuration error should be reported

    Scenario: Read Xray reference test plan configuration

        Given 'XC_DEFAULT_TEST_PLAN' environment variable has been set to 'DEFAULT_TEST_PLAN'
        When  Xray Connector reads Xray reference test plan configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'DEFAULT_TEST_PLAN'

    Scenario: Read Xray environment configuration

        Given 'XC_TEST_ENVIRONMENT' environment variable has been set to 'TEST_ENVIRONMENT'
        When  Xray Connector reads Xray environment configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'TEST_ENVIRONMENT'

    Scenario: Read feature files download directory configuration

        Given 'XC_FEATURES_DOWNLOAD_DIRECTORY' environment variable has been set to 'FEATURES_DOWNLOAD_DIRECTORY'
        When  Xray Connector reads feature files download directory configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'FEATURES_DOWNLOAD_DIRECTORY'

    Scenario: Read feature individual execution reports directory configuration

        Given 'XC_FEATURES_REPORT_DIRECTORY' environment variable has been set to 'FEATURES_REPORT_DIRECTORY'
        When  Xray Connector reads feature individual execution reports directory configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'FEATURES_REPORT_DIRECTORY'

    Scenario: Read merged execution report directory configuration

        Given 'XC_MERGED_REPORT_DIRECTORY' environment variable has been set to 'MERGED_REPORT_DIRECTORY'
        When  Xray Connector reads merged execution report directory configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'MERGED_REPORT_DIRECTORY'

    Scenario: Read gatling reports directory

        Given 'XC_GATLING_REPORTS_DIRECTORY' environment variable has been set to 'GATLING_REPORTS_DIRECTORY'
        When  Xray Connector reads gatling reports directory configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'GATLING_REPORTS_DIRECTORY'

    Scenario: Read gatling simulation main class

        Given 'XC_GATLING_SIMULATION' environment variable has been set to 'GATLING_SIMULATION'
        When  Xray Connector reads gatling simulation main class configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'GATLING_SIMULATION'

    Scenario: Read gatling report url

        Given 'XC_GATLING_REPORT_URL' environment variable has been set to 'GATLING_REPORT_URL'
        When  Xray Connector reads gatling report url configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'GATLING_REPORT_URL'

    Scenario: Read test plan file

        Given 'XC_TEST_PLAN_FILE' environment variable has been set to 'TEST_PLAN_FILE'
        When  Xray Connector reads test plan file configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'TEST_PLAN_FILE'

    Scenario: Read test labels

        Given 'XC_TEST_LABELS' environment variable has been set to 'TEST_LABEL1,TEST_LABEL2'
        When  Xray Connector reads test labels configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'TEST_LABEL1,TEST_LABEL2'

    Scenario: Read test fix versions (set with environment variables)

        Given 'XC_TEST_FIX_VERSIONS' environment variable has been set to 'TEST_FIX_VERSION1,TEST_FIX_VERSION2'
        When  Xray Connector reads test fix versions configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'TEST_FIX_VERSION1,TEST_FIX_VERSION2'

    Scenario: Read test fix versions (set with setTestFixVersions)

        Given The test fix versions are 'TEST_FIX_VERSION1,TEST_FIX_VERSION2'
        When  Xray Connector reads test fix versions configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'TEST_FIX_VERSION1,TEST_FIX_VERSION2'

    Scenario: Default JIRA host address

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_HOST' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA host configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'jira.dt.renault.com'

    Scenario: Report undefined Xray reference test plan configuration

        Given 'XC_DEFAULT_TEST_PLAN' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads Xray reference test plan configuration
        Then  A configuration error should be reported

    Scenario: Accept undefined Xray environment configuration

        Given 'XC_TEST_ENVIRONMENT' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads Xray environment configuration
        Then  The value returned should be undefined

    Scenario: Default feature files download directory

        Given 'XC_FEATURES_DOWNLOAD_DIRECTORY' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads feature files download directory configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'downloaded-features'

    Scenario: Default feature individual execution reports directory

        Given 'XC_FEATURES_REPORT_DIRECTORY' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads feature individual execution reports directory configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'reports/cucumber/features'

    Scenario: Default merged execution report directory

        Given 'XC_MERGED_REPORT_DIRECTORY' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads merged execution report directory configuration
        Then  The value returned should be 'reports/cucumber/merged'

    Scenario: Report lack of authentication information (no login)

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_LOGIN' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA credentials configuration
        Then  A configuration error should be reported

    Scenario: Report lack of authentication information (no token and no password)

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_TOKEN' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA credentials configuration
        Then  A configuration error should be reported

    Scenario: Authentication information can be made of token only (no login/password)

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_LOGIN' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_TOKEN' environment variable has been set to 'TOKEN'
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA credentials configuration
        Then  No configuration error should be reported

    Scenario: Authentication information can be made of login/password only (or token)

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_LOGIN' environment variable has been set to 'LOGIN'
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD' environment variable has been set to 'PASSWORD'
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_TOKEN' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA credentials configuration
        Then  No configuration error should be reported

    Scenario: Authentication information can be made of login/password only (no token) - OLD variable name

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_LOGIN' environment variable has been set to 'LOGIN'
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWORD' environment variable has been unset
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_PASSWD' environment variable has been set to 'PASSWD'
        And   'JIRA_XRAY_TOKEN' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads JIRA credentials configuration
        Then  No configuration error should be reported

    Scenario: Default Xray test exection custom fields ids

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_HOST' environment variable has been unset
        When  Xray Connector reads Xray test execution custom fields ids configuration
        Then  The value returned should be '{"testExecutionIssueTypeId":10212,"testExecutionTestPlansFieldId":10268,"testExecutionTestEnvironmentsFieldId":10266}'

    Scenario: DT jira Xray test exection custom fields ids

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_HOST' environment variable has been set to 'jira.dt.renault.com'
        When  Xray Connector reads Xray test execution custom fields ids configuration
        Then  The value returned should be '{"testExecutionIssueTypeId":10212,"testExecutionTestPlansFieldId":10268,"testExecutionTestEnvironmentsFieldId":10266}'

    Scenario: Intra jira Xray test execution custom fields id

        Given 'JIRA_XRAY_HOST' environment variable has been set to 'jira.intra.renault.fr'
        When  Xray Connector reads Xray test execution custom fields ids configuration
        Then  The value returned should be '{"testExecutionIssueTypeId":10204,"testExecutionTestPlansFieldId":10226,"testExecutionTestEnvironmentsFieldId":10224}'
